A Nairobi court has given media houses seven days to respond to the suit filed by ODM Starehe MP nominee Steve Mbogo that seeks to bar them from linking him to a defilement case.Senior resident magistrate David Mbeja has asked The Star, Nation Media Group and the Standard Group to respond. The defilement case was lodged in 2009 at the Kibera law courts, but the matter ended up at the High Court, where he was cleared of the defilement charges.The case will come up again on July 13.